{"type":"message","id":"11c4b7b1","parentId":"a0cdaf3e","timestamp":"2026-04-09T02:12:39.380Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"Es gibt noch keine .gitignore im Workspace. Ich sollte eine erstellen mit best practices für Token/Secret-Erkennung.","thinkingSignature":""},{"type":"text","text":"Ah, es gibt noch keine `.gitignore`. Ich erstelle eine mit umfassenden Regeln für Tokens und Secrets:"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"tool_ZzkrHoWy25OyAftFhvYrcHsg","name":"write","arguments":{"content":".gitignore\n# ============================================\n# GITIGNORE - Mit Token & Secret Protection\n# ============================================\n\n# --- Umgebungsvariablen & Configs mit Secrets ---\n.env\n.env.local\n.env.*.local\n.env.development\n.env.production\n.env.test\n!.env.example\n\n# Config-Dateien die oft Secrets enthalten\nconfig.json\nsecrets.json\ncredentials.json\n*.credentials.json\nservice-account*.json\n\n# --- API Keys & Tokens (Pattern-basiert) ---\n# Generische Token-Patterns\n*token*\n*apikey*\n*api-key*\n*api_key*\n*secret*\n*password*\n*passwd*\n*private*\n\n# Spezifische Dateien\n*.pem\n*.key\n*.p12\n*.pfx\n*.crt\n*.cer\n*.der\nid_rsa\nid_rsa.pub\nid_dsa\nid_dsa.pub\nid_ecdsa\nid_ecdsa.pub\nid_ed25519\nid_ed25519.pub\n.known_hosts\n.ssh/\n\n# --- Cloud Provider Credentials ---\n# AWS\n.aws/\naws.credentials\n.aws-credentials\n\n# Azure\n.azure/\n*.publishsettings\n\n# GCP\ngcloud/\n*.gcloud.json\napplication_default_credentials.json\n\n# --- Database Credentials ---\n*.db\n*.sqlite\n*.sqlite3\ndatabase.yml\nmongod.conf\nredis.conf\n\n# --- AI/LLM Service Tokens ---\n.openai*\n.anthropic*\n.claude*\n.gemini*\n.cohere*\n.huggingface*\n*.openai.key\n*.anthropic.key\n\n# --- NPM/Node Tokens ---\n.npmrc\n.npmignore\n.yarnrc\n.yarn-integrity\n\n# --- Python Virtual Envs (können Secrets enthalten) ---\nvenv/\n.env/\n.venv/\nenv/\nENV/\n\n# --- IDE & Editor ---\n.idea/\n.vscode/\n*.swp\n*.swo\n*~\n.DS_Store\nThumbs.db\n\n# --- Logs & Temp ---\n*.log\nlogs/\ntmp/\ntemp/\n*.tmp\n*.temp\n\n# --- Build Output ---\ndist/\nbuild/\nnode_modules/\n__pycache__/\n*.pyc\n*.pyo\n*.egg-info/\n\n# --- Backup Dateien ---\n*.bak\n*.backup\n*.old\n*.orig\n\n# --- Lokale Test-Dateien ---\nlocal-test*\ntest-local*\ndev-only*\n","path":".gitignore"}}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"kimi-coding","model":"k2p5","usage":{"input":16799,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":16799,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1775700733513}}
{"type":"message","id":"5e6a2e08","parentId":"11c4b7b1","timestamp":"2026-04-09T02:12:39.405Z","message":{"role":"toolResult","toolCallId":"tool_ZzkrHoWy25OyAftFhvYrcHsg","toolName":"write","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Successfully wrote 1630 bytes to .gitignore"}],"isError":false,"timestamp":1775700759401}}
{"type":"message","id":"713552ef","parentId":"5e6a2e08","timestamp":"2026-04-09T02:13:02.203Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"Gut, die .gitignore ist erstellt. Jetzt sollte ich noch ein paar zusätzliche Empfehlungen geben, wie man Tokens am besten handhabt.","thinkingSignature":""},{"type":"text","text":"✅ **`.gitignore` erstellt!**\n\nDie Datei enthält jetzt:\n\n### 🔐 Token/Secret-Schutz\n- `.env*` – Alle Umgebungsvariablen-Dateien\n- `*token*`, `*apikey*`, `*secret*` – Pattern-basierte Filter\n- SSH-Keys (`id_rsa`, `.pem`, `.key`)\n- Cloud-Credentials (AWS, Azure, GCP)\n- AI-Service-Keys (OpenAI, Anthropic, etc.)\n\n### 💡 Best Practices für Tokens:\n\n**1. `.env.example` als Template**\n```bash\n# Kopieren: .env.example → .env (lokal, nie commiten!)\nOPENAI_API_KEY=sk-...\nDATABASE_URL=postgresql://...\n```\n\n**2. Secrets in Code vermeiden**\n```python\n# ❌ FALSCH\napi_key = \"sk-abc123...\"\n\n# ✅ RICHTIG\nimport os\napi_key = os.getenv(\"OPENAI_API_KEY\")\n```\n\n**3. Pre-commit Hook (empfohlen)**\n```bash\n# Installiere git-secrets\ngit secrets --install\ngit secrets --register-aws  # Für AWS-Keys\n```\n\n### 🚀 Quick Check\n```bash\n# Zeigt was ignoriert wird\ngit check-ignore -v token.txt\n\n# Teste ob Secrets committed sind\ngit log --all --full-history -- .env\n```\n\nWillst du noch einen **pre-commit Hook** einrichten, der automatisch blockiert wenn Secrets erkannt werden?"}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"kimi-coding","model":"k2p5","usage":{"input":14403,"output":369,"cacheRead":3072,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":17844,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"stop","timestamp":1775700759406}}
