{"type":"message","id":"388b4219","parentId":"0e9c7d07","timestamp":"2026-04-09T03:19:40.626Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"Ah, I see the issue now. There's a cron job running every 5 minutes (`everyMs: 300000`) and it's enabled. The user is getting constant reminders even though there's nothing to sync.\n\nI should suggest disabling this job or increasing the interval to something more reasonable (like every 30 minutes or hourly) since:\n1. It's running every 5 minutes\n2. There's nothing new to sync (0 synced, 18 skipped)\n3. It's annoying for the user\n\nLet me explain this to the user and suggest disabling it or changing the interval.","thinkingSignature":""},{"type":"text","text":"Die alle-5-Minuten-Reminder kommen aus einem **Cron-Job** (`session-auto-sync-v2`). Das ist viel zu oft — vor allem wenn nichts zu syncen ist!\n\n## Aktueller Zustand:\n- **Intervall:** Alle 5 Minuten (`300000ms`)\n- **Status:** Aktiviert (`enabled: true`)\n- **Ergebnis:** 0 neue Sessions, 18 übersprungen\n\n## Optionen:\n\n### 1. **Cron-Job komplett deaktivieren** (empfohlen für jetzt)\n```json\n\"enabled\": false\n```\n→ Keine automatischen Reminder mehr. Du syncst manuell wenn nötig.\n\n### 2. **Intervall erhöhen** (z.B. auf 1x pro Stunde)\n```json\n\"everyMs\": 3600000  // 1 Stunde statt 5 Minuten\n```\n\n### 3. **Nur bei Änderungen syncen**\nDer Job könnte smarter sein — nur laufen wenn wirklich neue Sessions existieren.\n\n---\n\n**Soll ich den Job deaktivieren oder das Intervall ändern?** \n\nFür Option 1 oder 2 müsste ich die `jobs.json` bearbeiten."}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"kimi-coding","model":"k2p5","usage":{"input":3755,"output":399,"cacheRead":28416,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":32570,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"stop","timestamp":1775704761756}}
